alert.note: Alert for King (Washington) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.headline: Flood Warning issued March 01 at 10:59PM PST until March 02 at 10:46PM PST by NWS Seattle
info.description: ...The Flood Warning is extended for the following rivers in Washington... Green River Near Auburn affecting King County. .Rain in the forecast into Thursday will not be enough to stop the river from receding the next couple of days. ...FLOOD WARNING NOW IN EFFECT UNTIL LATE TOMORROW EVENING... * WHAT...Minor flooding is occurring and minor flooding is forecast. * WHERE...Green River Near Auburn. * WHEN...Until late tomorrow evening. * IMPACTS...At 9000.0 cfs, the Green River will flood low areas of the middle Green River valley with water over SE Green Valley Rd. Some backwater inundation is possible in lower Mill Creek basin between Auburn and Kent. A flow of 9000 cfs feet on the Green River corresponds to a phase 3 flood in the King County flood system. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 9:45 PM PST Tuesday the flow was 9290.0 cfs. - The river crested around 9700 cfs around 2 pm Tuesday. - Forecast...The river is expected to continue to recede tonight then stay near flood stage Wednesday morning. The river will drop below flood stage Wednesday afternoon. - Flood flow is 9000.0 cfs. - http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood &&
info.instruction: Motorists should not attempt to drive around barricades or drive cars through flooded areas. Flooding is occurring or is imminent. Most flood related deaths occur in automobiles. Do not attempt to cross water covered bridges, dips, or low water crossings. Never try to cross a flowing stream, even a small one, on foot. To escape rising water find another route over higher ground. Caution is urged when walking near riverbanks. Turn around, don`t drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood deaths occur in vehicles. Additional information is available at www.weather.gov. The next statement will be issued by Wednesday morning at 700 AM PST.
